                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/5773: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-05T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 5, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. Referring to Goold’s telegrams Nos. 136, 143, 145 and 147<note n="69"
                        xml:id="d664fn69">Nos. 145 and 147 not printed.</note> concerning an
                    increasing control and influence exercised by Germany and Italy in French
                    Morocco the Department will appreciate receiving by telegraph some more detailed
                    examination of the extent and form which that reported control and influence are
                    taking. Such an analysis, which should be prepared by you in collaboration with
                    Casablanca, should include, in addition to any facts in support of Goold’s
                    conclusions, any opinions which may be available on those conclusions from
                    responsible sources in Morocco.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
